**Version Used**: csc 3.6.0-2.20173.3 (2242fa4f) / VS 16.6.0 Preview 2.0

**Steps to Reproduce**:

Create a .NET Core 3.1 console project with following code:

```c#
using System;

class Program
{
    static void Main()
    {
        string? foo = null;
        var bar = foo ?? String.Empty;
        var baz = bar ?? String.Empty;

        var b = bar.Length;
        var z = baz.Length;
    }
}
```

**Expected Behavior**:

"var b = bar.Length" should not give warning CS8602  Dereference of a possibly null reference

**Actual Behavior**:

"var b = bar.Length" gives warning CS8602  Dereference of a possibly null reference

